commit.message: Updated changelog file with release date

Fix list size after double removal of a node

Removed nodes will now have their `prev`, `next` and `list` attributes set to
None.

This also prevents a bug where list size would be decremented after attempting
to remove the same node twice. The second operation will now raise a
`ValueError`.

Closes issue #6.

Support for Python 3.x

Also bumped package version to 0.3, since the change is large enough to warrant
a new release.

Closes issue #5.

Test corrections and refactoring

Some of the tests for 'cmp' comparison worked only because of some Python 2
quirks. They have been updated to reflect the correct behavior.

Refactored some tests to use floor division when calculating list indexes.

Also refactored tests for 'iternext' and 'iterprev' methods.

Updated changelog file with release date

Also reformatted an old log entry to fix a sphinx warning.

Fix updating of 'first' and 'last' property

The 'first' and 'last' list nodes weren't correctly updated by several methods.
Unit tests have been extended to validate these properties after each mutable
operation.

Closes issue #3.
Fix author list in package metadata
Fix typos in changelog and docs
